1439
01:22:58.316 --> 01:23:01.916
Probably not as much in breast or in colon, but with the whole body

1440
01:23:02.036 --> 01:23:05.926
MRIs. In order to just get a human through a whole body MRI in a way that isn't

1441
01:23:05.936 --> 01:23:09.736
going to keep them there for eight hours, we're by definition not scanning

1442
01:23:09.796 --> 01:23:11.776
every part of the body as well as we would like.

1443
01:23:12.416 --> 01:23:15.556
And so, all of us have those examples of misses.

1444
01:23:15.636 --> 01:23:18.196
I have a recent patient who on her

1445
01:23:19.516 --> 01:23:23.316
whole body had an eight centimeter leiomyosarcoma that on retrospect was a

1446
01:23:23.396 --> 01:23:27.386
little something the year prior. And so that's really, in my opinion, where I

1447
01:23:27.386 --> 01:23:30.866
think the test will help us, is that the imaging just

1448
01:23:30.996 --> 01:23:34.695
still isn't going to be, I think, as good as we could maybe find

1449
01:23:34.736 --> 01:23:38.476
something in the blood. I will point out that I do

1450
01:23:38.536 --> 01:23:42.076
think that it's an important point when we think about some of our

1451
01:23:42.156 --> 01:23:44.176
other inherited risk populations.

1452
01:23:44.436 --> 01:23:46.916
Colonoscopies and mammograms work really, really well.

1453
01:23:47.346 --> 01:23:50.846
And so whether or not these tests are going to be beneficial on top of those

1454
01:23:50.896 --> 01:23:54.736
well-established modalities, I think is less clear.

1455
01:23:54.756 --> 01:23:57.896
But where I look at in that is that particularly for breast, it could perhaps

1456
01:23:57.916 --> 01:24:01.776
really help us with the false positive rate, who should be biopsied, and most

1457
01:24:01.816 --> 01:24:05.686
importantly, when should a woman consider a bilateral mastectomy, and these

1458
01:24:05.716 --> 01:24:08.996
sorts of things. These assays might be able to help some of those decisions.

